description: Centre initiated the first structured talks with Meitei and Kuki representatives to resolve ethnic conflict in Manipur. The meeting focused on restoring peace, rebuilding trust, and addressing road blockades. However, COCOMI criticized the talks as a mere political exercise.
title: Centre holds Manipur peace meet; Meitei body calls it a ‘sham’

description: Karnataka deputy chief minister DK Shivakumar is adamant about retaining his role as KPCC president amidst internal power struggles within the Congress party. Delhi leadership has expressed support for him, at least temporarily. Shivakumar's stance is linked to his ambition to become chief minister, and he faces opposition from ministers loyal to CM Siddaramaiah.
title: DKS refuses to quit as Karnataka Congress chief, turf war intensifies

description: Authorities in Madhya Pradesh are investigating a man posing as a UK-trained cardiologist who is alleged to have performed fatal surgeries, leading to at least seven deaths. The suspect, whose real name may be Narendra Vikramaditya Yadav, has gone missing and lacked valid medical credentials.
title: Fake 'UK doctor' did heart surgeries, may have killed 7

description: The Waqf (Amendment) Bill's passage in Parliament has ignited intense political debates in Bihar ahead of the assembly elections. The bill's support by JDU and its opposition by RJD have led to heated exchanges, poster wars, and both parties outlining their positions vigorously, with the Grand Alliance vowing to scrap the bill if elected.
title: Waqf Bill: Who's the 'girgit'? Lalu, Nitish parties slug it out

description: The Indian government is carefully negotiating a trade deal with the US to ensure a balanced and mutually beneficial agreement. Despite US pressure to reduce tariffs, India aims to maintain its stance on sensitive sectors. Talks with other countries for trade agreements are ongoing, with limited capacity for new negotiations.
title: 'Win-win for both sides': In trade pact with US, India to protect domestic interests

description: After the Waqf Amendment Bill was passed following intense debates, legal disputes have emerged with multiple petitions filed in the Supreme Court claiming the bill is unconstitutional. Petitioners argue the changes infringe upon Muslim minority rights and undermine the autonomy of their religious institutions.
title: Battle over waqf bill reaches SC with blitz of petitions

description: To counter Donald Trump's reciprocal tariffs, Indian companies, including Apple, significantly boosted goods exports to the US, close to last year's $437 billion target. Sectors like electronics, gems, and apparel saw a marked increase in shipments. India's total goods and services exports reached an estimated $800 billion for the fiscal year, with hopes of reduced uncertainty ahead.
title: Flurry of exports as firms race to beat Trump tariffs

description: Nine years after Ashwini Bidre-Gore's disappearance, inspector Abhay Kurundkar has been convicted of her murder by the Panvel sessions court. The court found him guilty of killing Bidre in 2016, dismembering her body, and dumping it in Vasai creek. Two others were also convicted for helping dispose of the body.
title: Maharashtra: Cop convicted of killing API lover, dumping body

description: A month after Manav Sharma's suicide in Agra, his wife Nikita and her father were arrested in Ahmedabad. Manav, who left behind a video accusing his wife of harassment, had been threatened by her family. The emotional video highlighted the isolation faced by men in troubled marriages.
title: Month after techie killed self in Agra, wife & her dad held in Ahmedabad

description: Indian Air Force Warrant Officer Ramkumar Tiwari, 41, from Uttar Pradesh, died during a routine para jumping exercise in Agra due to a parachute malfunction. Despite being taken to the Military Hospital, he succumbed to his injuries. He is survived by his wife and two children. Tiwari will receive full military honors during his cremation.
title: IAF warrant officer dies during para jumping in Agra

description: The Karnataka high court has pushed for the implementation of the Uniform Civil Code (UCC) to ensure equal gender justice across communities. Justice Hanchate Sanjeevkumar highlighted discrepancies in inheritance rights under Hindu and Muslim laws. The court ruled in favor of a deceased Muslim woman's husband, allotting him a 75% share of her properties, while urging legislative action on UCC.
title: Karnataka high court bats for UCC, says will ensure gender justice for all

description: Indian Navy is committed to preventing dominance by any nation in the Indian Ocean Region through its military and economic strength. Defence Minister Rajnath Singh highlights India's efforts for peace, stability, and free navigation, emphasizing the Navy's role in protecting interests without compromising sovereignty.
title: Under India watch, no one can be IOR 'bully': Rajnath Singh

description: LeBron James appeared injured in the Lakers' 116-123 loss to the Warriors, raising concerns about team chemistry. The Warriors, boosted by Jimmy Butler's addition, are surging, while the Lakers, despite acquiring Luka Doncic and Anthony Davis, struggle with inconsistency. With playoffs approaching, Lakers must address their defensive lapses and team cohesion.
title: LeBron left stunned as Lakers teammates ignore injury in shocking loss to Warriors
Musk breaks silence on Trump tariffs, slams key White House adviser

description: Donald Trump has boasted of an 'economic revolution' resulting in $5 trillion investment into the US, despite the US stock market losing $11 trillion since January 20. Critics blame his tariff policies for the market's downfall, while Trump insists they will recover manufacturing jobs and economic stability.
title: Trump tees off with tariff bogey amid meltdown in US markets

description: Residents of Dehradun's Miyanwala area, predominantly from the Rajput community, are opposing the proposal to rename the area as Ramjiwala, citing its deep historical significance. They emphasize that the name does not have Mughal connections but rather honors their ancestral heritage.
title: Uttarakhand: Miyanwala not tied to Mughals, do not rename it, say locals
Watch: Thousands at protest against Trump, Musk as ‘Hands Off!’ movement begins

description: India signed its first ever MoU for defence cooperation with Sri Lanka to strengthen military ties. PM Narendra Modi's visit also saw agreements on energy inter-connectivity and developing Trincomalee as an energy hub. Additionally, India announced debt restructuring and reduced interest rates on loans, showing support for Sri Lanka’s economic and social development.
title: Won't let our land be used against India: SL President
BJP protests over worker’s suicide in Karnataka, wants 2 Cong MLAs named in FIR

description: Alert BSF forces thwarted an infiltration attempt, killing a Pakistani intruder crossing into the RS Pura sector of Jammu. Despite warnings, the intruder persisted and was shot dead. A flag meeting with Pakistan Rangers followed, who refused to accept the body. Security officials are enhancing measures in the region.
title: BSF foils infiltration bid, shoots dead Pak intruder along intl border in Jammu

description: Rajasthan Royals secured a convincing 50-run victory over Punjab Kings, largely due to Yashasvi Jaiswal’s impressive 67 runs and Jofra Archer’s impactful bowling. Archer’s aggressive spell resulted in crucial wickets, restricting Punjab to 155/9 in 20 overs and ensuring Rajasthan’s dominant win. Jaiswal’s 89-run stand with Sanju Samson (38 off 26) put RR in control early. And after both departed, Riyan Parag (43* off 25) and Shimron Hetmyer (20 off 12) ensured the momentum never dipped, powering the Royals past the 200-run mark.
title: IPL: Blazing Yashasvi, fiery Archer sink Punjab Kings in Mullanpur

description: The Omar Abdullah government faces criticism for requesting the HC to dismiss a petition challenging J&K’s high reservation policy, which limits access for open merit candidates. Minister Sakina Itoo suggested the affidavit was an error, promising a fresh one and affirming the government's commitment to reviewing the reservation system.
title: Omar Abdullah govt backs quota review outside, opposes it in court
President Murmu gives assent to Waqf Bill after Parliament clears it

description: Kerala BJP president Rajeev Chandrasekhar has accused Congress leader Rahul Gandhi of misusing the Constitution for spreading lies and acting against India's interests. Chandrasekhar also slammed Congress MPs for allegedly inciting communal hatred during the Waqf (Amendment) Bill debate and praised PM Modi for making Waqf land more accessible to the poor.
title: Rahul Gandhi 'acting against' India's interests, says BJP's Rajeev Chandrasekhar

description: Ja Morant of the Memphis Grizzlies is set to play against the Detroit Pistons, providing a much-needed boost for his team amidst their playoff push. Despite recent controversies and fines for inappropriate gestures, Morant's return may prove pivotal as the Grizzlies seek a crucial victory. The game will be broadcast at 7 p.m. ET on FDSDET, FDSSE, and NBA TV.
title: Will Ja Morant play tonight against the Detroit Pistons? Latest update injury report

description: CSK head coach Stephen Fleming dismissed criticism on Ravichandran Ashwin's YouTube channel following their defeat to DC. The comments questioned the choice of playing spinner Noor Ahmad over veterans. Fleming remained unperturbed, emphasizing the team's focus on on-field performance. CSK's loss marked their third consecutive defeat in IPL 2025, intensifying mid-table pressure.
title: 'Irrelevant': CSK's Fleming reacts to criticism on Ashwin’s YT channel

description: Chennai Super Kings head coach Stephen Fleming dismissed speculations about MS Dhoni's retirement, emphasising it’s not his role to decide Dhoni's IPL career's end. Fleming praised Dhoni's enduring performance despite a challenging match against Delhi Capitals, highlighting tough batting conditions and the need for stronger top-order contributions to support the power hitters.
title: 'Not my role to put an end to it': Fleming on Dhoni retirement buzz
AIMPLB plans nationwide stir against Waqf Bill

description: Chennai Super Kings lost to Delhi Capitals by 25 runs in their IPL 2025 match. Chasing 184, CSK struggled at 74/5 when MS Dhoni entered. Dhoni and Vijay Shankar added a slow 84-run partnership, failing to accelerate. KL Rahul's 77 off 51 balls powered Delhi to 183/6, maintaining their unbeaten run while CSK's campaign falters.
title: Dhoni, Shankar create unwanted records in CSK's sluggish chase vs DC

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi is visiting Tamil Nadu to inaugurate India's first vertical lift sea bridge in Rameswaram and launch major infrastructure projects worth Rs 8,300 crore. He will also offer prayers at Ramanathaswamy Temple and address a public gathering.
title: PM Modi to inaugurate Pamban rail bridge, other projects in TN: Key details

description: Mark Zuckerberg, Jeff Bezos, and Elon Musk experienced massive financial losses totaling $42.6 billion due to new tariffs announced by President Trump. The introduction of tariffs led to a steep decline in major US stock indexes, reflecting heightened investor concerns over their impact on business costs and global trade.
title: Musk, Bezos and Zuckerberg lose $42.6bn after Trump's ‘discounted’ tariffs go 'live'

description: Celebrities attended Manoj Kumar's state funeral, dignifying his patriotic legacy. RJ Mahvash sparked dating rumors with Yuzvendra Chahal through a supportive video. Saif Ali Khan’s stabbing case intensified as the accused's bail was denied. Vin Diesel shared a throwback photo with Deepika Padukone, exciting fans. Tony Kakkar's new song, linked to Samay Raina, continues to stir discussions.
title: Celebs attend Manoj Kumar's funeral: Top 5 entertainment news

description: Delhi Capitals achieved a historic win over Chennai Super Kings at MA Chidambaram Stadium after 15 years, marking their third consecutive IPL 2025 victory. KL Rahul's 77 and a solid team effort led to a 25-run win, pushing DC to the top of the points table, while CSK faced their third straight defeat.
title: History! DC finally break 15-year curse against CSK in Chennai

description: KL Rahul's 77 off 51 anchored Delhi Capitals' win over Chennai Super Kings by 25 runs, marking their first victory at Chepauk in 15 years. Despite early setbacks, DC posted 183/6. CSK stumbled during their chase, with disciplined bowling from DC limiting them to 158/5. DC secured their third consecutive win, strengthening their position as early title contenders.
title: KL Rahul masterclass powers DC to historic win over CSK at Chepauk

description: Shiv Sena (UBT) MP Sanjay Raut announced that the party will not contest the Waqf Amendment Bill, 2025, in the Supreme Court, considering the matter closed. While the Shiv Sena (UBT) steps back, other leaders including AIMIM MP Asaduddin Owaisi and Congress leader Mohammad Jawed have already filed petitions challenging the Bill.
title: Sanjay Raut says Shiv Sena (UBT) won't move SC against Waqf Bill

description: Punjab Kings captain Shreyas Iyer decided to bowl first against Rajasthan Royals in their IPL 2025 clash at Mullanpur. Rajasthan welcomed back Sanju Samson as captain while pacer Tushar Deshpande missed the fixture due to a niggle, with Yudhvir Singh Charak included as his replacement. Pacer Tushar Deshpande missed the fixture due to a niggle, and Yudhvir Singh Charak was included in the XI as his replacement.
title: Sanju Samson captains Rajasthan Royals for the first time in IPL 2025

description: Hardik Pandya was emotional after Mumbai Indians lost a close IPL 2025 match against Lucknow Super Giants by 12 runs. Pandya's career-best performance with the ball (5/36) had restricted LSG to 203/8, but MI fell short despite strong contributions from Suryakumar Yadav, Naman Dhir, and Tilak Varma, struggling to find boundaries in the final overs.
title: Watch: Pandya struggles to hold back emotions after LSG defeat

description: Microsoft's 50th anniversary was disrupted by two Pro-Palestine protests from employees criticizing the company's ties to Israel. Software engineers Ibtihal Aboussad and Vaniya Agrawal accused Microsoft of providing technology that supports violence in Gaza. The protests were part of a larger movement within the company, urging Microsoft to end its relationship with Israel.
title: Microsoft's 50th anniversary celebrations hit by Pro-Palestine protests

description: Digvesh Singh Rathi’s bowling career transformed after being rejected at the Delhi and District Cricket Association trials. Driven by the goal to avoid conceding sixes, Rathi honed his skills in local games. His persistence paid off when he was picked by Lucknow Super Giants in IPL, impressing with his economical bowling and determination.
title: Digvesh Rathi: From watching Narine videos to becoming Pant’s ace

description: India, UAE, and Sri Lanka have signed an agreement to develop Trincomalee as an energy hub, during PM Modi’s visit to Colombo. The project will involve a multi-product pipeline and utilization of an old oil tank farm. The collaboration is seen as a strategic move to counter China’s growing influence in Sri Lanka.
title: Eye on China: India, UAE & Sri Lanka to develop energy hub

description: Defence Minister Rajnath Singh emphasized India's role in maintaining peace and stability in the Indian Ocean Region amid China's strategic presence. The Indian Navy's launch of the 'Indian Ocean ship (IOS) Sagar' underscores India's commitment to secure navigation and shared interests. With a diverse crew visiting various ports, it reflects India's dedication to collective security and prosperity.
title: Indian Navy ensures no nation suppresses another in IOR : Rajnath

description: President Trump has reiterated his tariff policies, asserting that China has borne a heavier impact than the US in their trade conflict. Following China's imposition of reciprocal tariffs, Trump emphasized the alleged economic benefits and job growth in the United States, while dismissing China's retaliatory measures as a sign of panic.
title: 'It won’t be easy': Trump asks Americans to 'hang tough' amid escalating tariff war

description: Wayne Gretzky’s locker room speech fired up Team Canada, who won the 4 Nations Face-Off final. However, some fans criticized his perceived closeness with Donald Trump, leading to public backlash. Despite the controversy, Gretzky’s contributions to hockey and his love for Canada remain undisputed.
title: Janet Jones recalls Wayne Gretzky's locker room speech before USA-Canada 4 Nations finals

description: Union Home Minister Amit Shah announced that Naxalism will be eradicated in India by March 2026, highlighting the BJP government's ongoing efforts. Over 880 Naxals surrendered in 2024, with promises to reintegrate those who lay down arms. Shah emphasized development in Bastar and honored tribal artists for their cultural contributions.
title: 'Naxalism will be eradicated from India by March 2026': Amit Shah in Bastar

description: Salman Khan’s much-anticipated Eid release Sikandar, also starring Rashmika Mandanna, is having a tough run at the box office. Despite the festive release on March 30 and high expectations, the film has struggled to cross the Rs 100 crore milestone in its first week, a figure it was expected to surpass with ease. On day 7 (Saturday), early estimates indicate a net collection of Rs 1.53 crore across all languages.
title: Sikandar box office collection day 7: Salman Khan's Eid release earns only Rs 1.53 crore
Turmoil in BJD: Patnaik urged to act against party MP over Waqf Bill

description: Digvesh Rathi, a spinner for Lucknow Super Giants, has stirred controversy in IPL 2025 with his provocative 'notebook' celebration. After being fined for unsportsmanlike conduct against the Punjab Kings, he repeated the gesture against Mumbai Indians, facing increased penalties. Rathi has been fined Rs 5,62,500 and accumulated three demerit points, sparking debate on player conduct.
title: IPL: How much has Digvesh Rathi been fined for celebrating?

description: Six-year-old Pihu’s future is uncertain as a custody battle ensues between the families of her deceased father, ex-merchant navy officer Saurabh Rajput, and her accused mother, Muskan Rastogi. While her maternal grandparents care for her, her paternal uncle seeks legal custody. Muskan allegedly murdered Saurabh with her lover, making the situation even more complex.
title: Meerut murder: Custody battle for 6-yr-old daughter intensifies

description: Israel tried to avoid the tariffs by announcing that it would lift all tariffs on US products. But Trump announced a 17 per cent tariff on Isreal.If Netanyahu meets Trump in the White House on Monday, he will be the first foreign leader to visit Trump in person to negotiate on tariffs.
title: Netanyahu planning to visit Trump to negotiate 17% tariff: Report

description: Delhi BJP chief Virendra Sachdeva accused former CM Arvind Kejriwal of having an extravagant lifestyle at the taxpayers' expense, presenting RTI data showing an average annual maintenance cost of over Rs 3.69 crore for his official residence from 2015 to 2022. The AAP has yet to respond to the allegations.
title: 'Over Rs 29cr spent ...': BJP's fresh attack on Kejriwal in Sheesh Mahal row

description: After Pakistan's 3-0 ODI loss to New Zealand, Khushdil Shah faced verbal abuse from Afghan spectators, leading to a confrontational incident. The situation was defused when officials ejected the disruptive fans. Pakistan's loss was marked by the batting collapse and Ben Sears' remarkable 5/34 performance. PCB's response emphasized the need to maintain respect in cricket.
title: Watch: Khushdil attacks spectator after anti-Pakistan taunts

description: RJD leader Tejashwi Yadav condemned the Waqf Amendment Bill, 2025, as unconstitutional, accusing BJP of promoting division and distracting from key issues. The Bill, which passed Parliament, aims to enhance transparency and governance of Waqf institutions while cutting mandatory contributions and ensuring women's inheritance.
title: 'BJP wants to divide country': Tejashwi Yadav slams Waqf Bill as 'unconstitutional'

description: Delhi's BJP-led administration has partnered with the central government to adopt the Ayushman Bharat Pradhan Mantri Jan Arogya Yojana. The healthcare scheme will provide eligible Delhi households with annual health insurance worth Rs 10 lakh. This makes Delhi the 35th state/Union Territory to implement this health programme.
title: Delhi govt rolls out Centre's Ayushman Bharat scheme, card distribution from April 10

description: Stand-up comedian Kunal Kamra queries BookMyShow about his removal from their list of artists following controversial remarks against Maharashtra deputy CM Eknath Shinde. This comes after Shiv Sena's Rahool Kanal thanked BookMyShow for removing Kamra, highlighting the conflict where Shiv Sainiks vandalized Kamra's performance studio.
title: 'It's fine': Kamra reacts to Shiv Sena's 'BookMyShow removed him' claim

description: Speculation about MS Dhoni's retirement intensified as his parents and wife attended the match against the Delhi Capitals at Chepauk Stadium. With the emotional backdrop at his home ground, fans are wondering if this might be his farewell game in the IPL. Dhoni has featured in 267 IPL matches, batting in 232 innings and amassing 5,289 runs at an impressive average of 39.18 and a strike rate of 137.70.
title: MS Dhoni to retire? Legends’ parents make rare appearance at Chepauk

description: Delhi Capitals will play without vice-captain Faf du Plessis in their crucial match against Chennai Super Kings due to fitness issues. Despite this, captain Axar Patel won the toss and chose to bat first as DC looks to continue its winning momentum, while CSK aims to recover from recent defeats.
title: Axar Patel drops big-hitting star for CSK clash — Here's why

description: After suffering a 3-0 series defeat to New Zealand, Mohammad Rizwan urges Pakistan to focus on the upcoming Pakistan Super League (PSL). Despite individual flashes of form from Babar Azam and Naseem Shah, Pakistan's batting struggled against New Zealand's strong attack. Rizwan remains optimistic, emphasizing PSL as an opportunity for Pakistan to regain confidence.
title: 'CT, NZ series loss in past; Pakistan will now enjoy PSL': Rizwan

description: The Enforcement Directorate (ED) conducted a multi-state search operation on Friday, recovering Rs 1.5 crore in Tamil Nadu and Kerala. The operation is part of an investigation into suspected violations of the Foreign Exchange Management Act (FEMA) by Gokulam Gopalan's Sree Gopalan Chit and Finance Co. Ltd.
title: ED seizes Rs 1.5 crore in FEMA case linked to 'Empuraan' producer

description: Scientist Inna Birchenko began to cry as she described the smouldering protected forest in Thailand where she was collecting samples from local trees shrouded in wildfire smoke. Birchenko and her colleagues hiked kilometre after kilometre through burned or still-smouldering forest, each footstep stirring up columns of black and grey ash.
title: 'It's gone': Conservation science in Thailand's burning forest

description: J P Morgan projects a US recession by the end of 2025, attributing it to President Trump's new reciprocal tariffs. The forecast indicates a potential GDP decline and higher unemployment. Federal Reserve Chair Jerome Powell echoed the concerns, highlighting that tariffs may cause higher inflation and slower growth.
title: JP Morgan predicts US recession by 2025-end due to Trump tariffs

description: During the final ODI between Pakistan and New Zealand at Bay Oval, a bizarre floodlight failure occurred mid-delivery, causing temporary confusion. Pakistan was chasing 265 but faltered, ending at 221, with key performances from Babar Azam and Mohammad Rizwan. Despite initial solid efforts, Pakistan's middle and lower order collapsed, marking a tough tour overall.
title: Lights out! Pak vs NZ observes bizarre power cut - Watch

description: Fans at MA Chidambaram Stadium in Chennai were anticipating Mahendra Singh Dhoni to lead the toss but were met with Ruturaj Gaikwad instead. Dhoni, also known as 'Thala', has passed the captaincy baton to Gaikwad for Chennai Super Kings' IPL 2024 season. CSK’s IPL triumphs under Dhoni came in 2010, 2011, 2018, 2021, and 2023.
title: Ruturaj Gaikwad recovers from elbow injury, no Dhoni as captain

description: Mumbai Indians' head coach Mahela Jayawardene confirmed star opener Rohit Sharma missed the IPL 2025 match against Lucknow due to a knee injury from practice. Rohit’s inability to bat without discomfort led to the decision to rest him. His absence pressures the team as they seek to recover in a critical tournament phase.
title: 'Unfortunate what happened ...': MI coach shares details of Rohit's injury
What are Americans buying before Trump's tariffs kick in? Full list

description: Mumbai Indians retired out Tilak Varma during their IPL-2025 match against Lucknow Super Giants due to a finger injury which hampered his ability to hit powerfully. Coach Mahela Jayawardene deemed the tactical decision necessary, but MI eventually fell short of their 204-run chase. TOI has learnt that the decision, which seems harsh on the face of it on the talented batter, was purely taken as Tilak is suffering from a niggle in a finger.
title: Why Tilak Varma was retired out by Mumbai Indians

description: Justice Yashwant Varma took oath as a judge of Allahabad high court despite an ongoing in-house inquiry over semi-burnt cash recovered from his residence. There's no judicial work assigned for now. A PIL was filed to halt the ceremony, and the legal fraternity criticized the decision, urging the Chief Justice to reconsider until the investigation concludes.
title: Cash row: Justice Varma takes oath as Allahabad HC judge, but won't get work
'Shield of a true friend': PM Modi hails Colombo's big vow to India over territory

description: Rajkumar Singh, a 45-year-old watchman in Aligarh, has received a notice to pay Rs 2.2 crore in taxes due to the fraudulent use of his PAN card for large transactions. This incident follows similar cases affecting people from low-income backgrounds, prompting an ongoing investigation by the Income Tax department.
title: Now, watchman gets Rs 2.2 crore I-T notice in Aligarh; 4th case in 2 wks

description: AAP MLA Amanatullah Khan has approached the Supreme Court challenging the Waqf (Amendment) Bill 2025, claiming it limits religious and cultural autonomy of Muslims. Despite criticism from the INDIA bloc, the bill, aiming for secular and transparent Waqf administration, was passed by Parliament with significant majorities in both Lok Sabha and Rajya Sabha.
title: After Owaisi, AAP MLA Amanatullah Khan challenges Waqf Bill in SC

description: Himachal Pradesh has experienced a rise in both maximum and minimum temperatures over the past week, with several areas recording temperatures well above normal. The IMD has predicted a hot summer with increased heatwave days and expects deficient rainfall. Kullu received the highest rain, while Una recorded the lowest.
title: Himachal Pradesh hills feel the heat as maximum temp hits 'sizzling 30s'

description: Prime Minister Modi’s three-day visit to Sri Lanka fostered stronger bilateral ties with President Dissanayake. Seven MoUs were signed in key sectors including defence, energy, and trade. Modi received the Mithra Vibhushana medal, highlighting his role in regional cooperation and India’s support during Sri Lanka’s economic crisis.
title: PM Modi in Sri Lanka: India, SL sign 7 pacts; defence, energy in focus
Trump 'actively negotiating' tariffs with India, other nations: Report

description: Imam-ul-Haq was stretchered off after being struck on the jaw by a powerful throw during Pakistan's final ODI against New Zealand. He was diagnosed with a concussion and replaced by Usman Khan. Despite the injury, New Zealand's Ben Sears led his team to a 43-run victory, securing a series sweep.
title: Watch: Imam-ul-Haq suffers a gruesome blow on jaw in New Zealand

description: Birmingham faces 17,000 tonnes of uncollected rubbish due to a municipal workers' strike, which escalated from limited action in January to an indefinite strike. The dispute involves pay cuts affecting up to 150 workers by £8,000 annually. Overflowing bins and pests pose public health risks, drawing comparisons to the 1978 garbage strike.
title: Birmingham streets full of garbage, pests, and stink as workers strike drags on
Job loss for 25,752 teachers- Mamata and Bengal's moment of reckoning

description: Indian shooter Sift Kaur Samra claimed her first individual ISSF World Cup gold in the women's 50m rifle 3 positions in Buenos Aires. Despite a slow start, she made a stunning comeback and finished with 458.6 points. India now stand second in the season-opening World Cup with one gold and one bronze.
title: Sift Kaur Samra wins gold medal at ISSF World Cup in Buenos Aires

description: Tensions escalated in Imphal West as women protesters attempted to storm NPP state president Yumnam Joykumar Singh's residence over his controversial remarks. Singh's statement accusing Arambai Tenggol of attacking Kukis was retracted, and the NPP youth wing called it a misunderstanding, vowing to prevent such issues in the future.
title: Tensions in Manipur: Women protestors try to storm NPP chief's home

description: Lucknow Super Giants spinner Digvesh Singh Rathi has been fined 50 per cent of his match fee for violating the IPL code of conduct during their win over Mumbai Indians. This is his second penalty for the same offense. Additionally, LSG captain Rishabh Pant was fined ₹12 lakh for maintaining a slow over-rate in the match.
title: IPL: Rathi fined again for celebrations; Pant penalised for slow over-rate

description: The Karnataka 2nd PUC Result 2025 is expected to be announced in April. Students can check their results online via the official websites, karresults.nic.in and kseab.karnataka.gov.in/english. The result will be provisional, and the original mark sheet will be provided by schools. Following past trends, the results are typically declared in April, with the announcement expected around mid-month. Students should stay updated on the official websites for further details.
title: Karnataka 2nd PUC result 2025 on karresults.nic.in: When and how to check

description: Meta CEO Mark Zuckerberg experienced the largest decline in net worth on April 3, losing $17.9 billion. This massive loss occurred alongside a $208 billion collective drop in market value among the world's wealthiest individuals, triggered by US President Trump's new reciprocal tariffs causing market turmoil.
title: Tech CEO loses billions in a day as Wall Street Bleeds, & its Not Musk

description: The US government has reduced environmental protections for logging in over half of the national forests, citing wildfire risks. The new policy fast-tracks environmental assessments and eliminates the appeal process. This emergency measure covers 176,000 square miles of land, with high wildfire risks, and aims to address forest health crises and fire risks due to dense forests and pest infestations.
title: US cuts environmental protections across majority of national forests

description: A Russian missile strike on the residential area of Kryvyi Rih killed 18 people, including nine children, and wounded over two dozen others. Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy accuses Russia of deliberate attacks and neglecting ceasefire agreements. Russia confirmed the strike, claiming it targeted a restaurant where commanders and Western instructors were meeting.
title: Russian strike kills 18, including 9 children, in Zelenskyy's hometown

description: Microsoft celebrates its 50th anniversary with a conversation featuring Satya Nadella, Bill Gates, and Steve Ballmer, moderated by the AI assistant Copilot. The discussion includes playful roasts, reflections on AI's future, and gratitude for past leadership. Nadella expresses deep appreciation for the contributions of Bill, Steve, and Paul in building the company.
title: Satya Nadella shares when 3 Microsoft CEOs get interviewed 50th Anniversary

description: BSF troops neutralised an intruder attempting to cross the international border in Jammu and Kashmir. Despite repeated warnings, the individual continued advancing on the night of April 4 and 5, leading to decisive action by the BSF. An investigation is underway to determine the identity and motive of the intruder.
title: BSF shoots Pakistani intruder crossing Jammu border

description: Delhi Capitals (DC) share the lead with Punjab Kings early in the IPL 2025 season, while Chennai Super Kings (CSK) struggle with back-to-back losses. CSK captain Ruturaj Gaikwad's injury may lead MS Dhoni to step in. The spin-friendly pitch at Chepauk prompts anticipation for the upcoming match.
title: IPL match today: CSK vs DC in Chennai - all you need to know
US tariffs wipe out $9 trillion globally; Trump says will 'supercharge economy'

description: Mumbai Indians captain Hardik Pandya explained the decision to retire out Tilak Varma during their 12-run loss against Lucknow Super Giants. Pandya cited the need for quick runs as the reason behind the move. Mumbai Indians fell short despite Suryakumar Yadav's 67-run knock and Pandya's five-wicket haul, conceding crucial extra runs that proved to be decisive.
title: IPL 2025: Hardik Pandya explains reasoning behind retiring Tilak Varma

description: Tilak Varma was retired out in MI's match against LSG, scoring 25 off 23 balls in a chase of 204. MI head coach Mahela Jayawardene made the decision, citing Tilak's struggle for rhythm. Hardik Pandya supported the move, acknowledging the need for fresh energy. Eventually, MI fell short by 12 runs.
title: IPL 2025: Tilak Varma joins small, exclusive club during LSG vs MI

description: Salman Khan's Sikandar sees a sharp decline at the domestic box office, earning just Rs 3.75 crore on Day 6. Despite a strong start on Eid, the film's collections have been consistently falling. With a domestic total of Rs 94 crore, the film's performance is under scrutiny, especially comparing to Vicky Kaushal's Chhaava, nearing Rs 600 crore.
title: Sikandar box office collection day 6: Salman Khan starrer hits new low

description: A senior professor at Meerut College has been barred for life from examination and evaluation work by Chaudhary Charan Singh University. The action followed protests by RSS-linked students over an exam question that associated the RSS with religious and caste-based politics gains. Professor Panwar has apologised for the incident.
title: UP college professor banned for life from exam duties over questions on RSS

description: The Rajya Sabha passed the resolution confirming President's rule in Manipur after a heated debate. Union home minister Amit Shah criticized the opposition for politicizing the conflict, noting ongoing efforts for peace talks between the Meitei and Kuki communities. Opposition leaders criticized PM Modi for not visiting the violence-stricken state.
title: At 4am, Rajya Sabha confirms Prez rule in Manipur

description: A Delhi court has requested a status report from Tihar Jail following allegations by Christian Michel James, suspected middleman in the AgustaWestland case, that attempts were made to poison him in prison. James, requesting enhanced security, claimed previous poisoning attempts in 2019. The court also ordered his medical examination at AIIMS Delhi to alleviate his post-surgery pain.
title: Agusta accused claims bid to poison him in Tihar jail

description: US tariffs on Chinese imports raise fears of a tech supply chain disruption, but AI company DeepSeek remains largely unaffected. DeepSeek's digital AI models and software aren't subject to traditional tariffs, and it focuses on data processing rather than manufacturing. However, the US may still impose restrictions due to national security concerns.
title: 2 reasons Trump tariffs are not a worry for DeepSeek

description: Sachin Bansal acknowledged his dissatisfaction with leaving Flipkart after Walmart's acquisition, labeling it as 'unfinished business.' Bansal faced disagreements with Walmart's focus on short-term sales. He now channels his ambition into Navi, a financial services startup, still aiming to create a large-scale impactful platform.
title: Flipkart co-founder admits disagreements with Walmart, says my exit was ...

description: The Indian high commission in Ottawa confirmed the fatal stabbing of an Indian national in Rockland, near Ottawa. Local police have taken a suspect into custody. The embassy is coordinating with community groups to provide support to the bereaved family, emphasizing their close contact with local authorities.
title: Indian national stabbed to death in Canada's Ottawa; suspect in custody

description: US secretary of state Marco Rubio stated that Greenlanders do not want to remain a part of Denmark and emphasized US concerns about Chinese influence in the region. Rubio highlighted Washington's respect for Greenland's self-determination while cautioning against Chinese economic involvement in Greenland.
title: US to Denmark: Greenlanders 'don't want to be part of you' anymore

description: California Governor Gavin Newsom announces plans to establish independent trade relations to counteract President Trump's tariffs. He emphasizes the state's economic significance and commitment to stable global partnerships, despite opposition from the White House.
title: Top US tech state rejects Trump Tariffs, sends global message

description: The security detail for Gursharan Kaur, wife of the late ex-PM Manmohan Singh, has been downgraded from Z-plus to Z by the Centre. This decision followed a recent review by intelligence agencies which assessed her reduced threat level. CRPF will continue to provide the scaled-down Z category protection.
title: Govt slashes security for wife of Manmohan Singh

description: Justin Vernon, frontman of Bon Iver, shared his emotional experience seeing fans sing “exile” from Taylor Swift’s folklore album during her Eras Tour. He reflected on his bond with Swift and their collaborations. Vernon praised the audience's powerful engagement and anticipates the release of Bon Iver’s fifth studio album, SABLE, fABLE on April 11.
title: Bon Iver’s Justin calls Taylor Swift’s ‘Exile’ performance an ‘out of body’ moment

description: US President Donald Trump posted a video showing an American airstrike that killed dozens of Houthi fighters in Yemen. The strike was a response to Houthi attacks on commercial and military vessels, allegedly supported by Iran. Over 200 strikes were carried out on Tuesday alone, with additional deployments announced.
title: Watch: Trump posts US airstrike video, says 'They won’t sink our ships again!'

description: Three Muslim JDU functionaries resigned over the party's support for the waqf bill in Bihar, raising concerns ahead of state elections. Despite the backlash, JDU believes welfare initiatives for minorities will secure votes. JDU has faced strained relations with Muslim voters after past support for controversial bills, but remains optimistic about its electoral prospects.
title: 5 netas quit JDU in Bihar, which will go to polls later this year

description: A 35-year-old woman and her two children, aged 6 and 5, were found dead on their house roof in Bisrakh. Police suspect she hanged herself after killing the children following a quarrel with her husband, Rajkumar. The couple, who had been married for 12 years, often fought over domestic issues. The bodies have been sent for autopsy.
title: ‘Quarrel over breakfast with husband’: Noida woman kills two kids, dies by suicide

description: Manoj Kumar, known for his patriotic roles in films like 'Upkar' and 'Kranti', passed away at 87 after battling health issues. Kumar's career included celebrated works in both nationalistic and crime dramas. His death was widely mourned, with Prime Minister Narendra Modi acknowledging his significant contribution to Indian cinema.
title: Manoj Kumar: Man who made ‘Bharat’ a screen hero

description: President Donald Trump disregarded market turmoil caused by new tariffs and reassured the public that his trade policies would ultimately benefit the US economy. Despite heavy losses in the stock market, Trump remained optimistic, claiming that short-term economic pain would result in long-term gains.
title: ‘Tariffs here to stay’: Trump says 'big business' not worried as markets lose $5tn

description: Apple has no immediate plans to change retail prices of its products in India and elsewhere despite new tariffs imposed by the Trump administration. This decision comes as Apple has sent an unusually high number of shipments to the US to build up stock and avoid the impact of higher tariffs.
title: Trump tariffs: Stocked-up Apple buys time, may not pass on duties soon

description: Indian officials face challenges in trade negotiations with Asean due to the presence of Chinese companies in the bloc. The issue echoes global concerns, particularly for the US, which has implemented high tariffs to curb Chinese economic dominance. This scenario complicates trade dynamics, especially with recent tariff retaliations from China.
title: Trump's China focus may open fresh opportunities for India

description: A 12-year-old girl from Odisha was allegedly raped by a fellow passenger in the toilet of an express train early Thursday. The incident was reported to the railway helpline and later to the Govt Railway Police at Secunderabad station. The accused, a 22-year-old from Bihar, was detained, and a case has been filed under the Pocso and IT Acts.
title: Bihar man rapes 12-year-old in train toilet, films it

description: A prime piece of land on Carmichael Road in south Mumbai has been sold to Mah-Hill Properties, an Adani Group subsidiary, for Rs 170 crore. Originally intended for a children's park, the plot is now designated for residential purposes. The deal involves Behram Nowrosji Gamadia, who inherited the property, and Mah-Hill Properties, with the transaction finalizing in late March.
title: Adani group firm buys 1-acre SoBo wooded plot for Rs 170 crore
